What is a server?
A server is a physical/virtual machine that runs an OS and is dedicated
to providing resources or other functionalities.

What is the role of the domain name?
A domain name is a human readable address used to locate and identify resources
such as websites on the internet

What type of DNS record www is in www.foobar.com?
www is configured as a CNAME record that acts as a subdomain which is mapped to
foobar.com

foobar.com is configured as an A record that is resolved to the IP address where
the webiste is located in the server

What is the role of the web server?
web server serves http requests with static pages

What is the role of the application server?
Application server role is to execute and manage business logic to serve dynamic
content from the database to client's requests

What is the role of the database?
A database is used to store data in a structured organised way that facilitates
easy retrival, management and modification

What is the server using to communicate with the computer of the user requesting the website?
The server is using a HTTP protocal over a network to communcate with the user
requesting the website